0 10:00:00", "open": 17.54641, "high": 17.54685, "low": 17.5227, "close": 17.52627}, {"time": "2026-07-20 11:00:00", "open": 17.52597, "high": 17.53086, "low": 17.51954, "close": 17.52409}, {"time": "2026-07-20 12:00:00", "open": 17.52471, "high": 17.52573, "low": 17.51089, "close": 17.51511}, {"time": "2026-07-20 13:00:00", "open": 17.51467, "high": 17.51635, "low": 17.50745, "close": 17.50919}, {"time": "2026-07-20 14:00:00", "open": 17.50885, "high": 17.51467, "low": 17.50741, "close": 17.51193}], "calendar": [], "editorial": "USD/MXN is trading at 17.5119 as the European session approaches its close, sitting just above a well-tested support cluster that has repeatedly attracted demand over recent sessions. The daily chart tells a story of a pair that broke sharply higher in late June \u2014 surging from the 17.30 area to a peak of 17.6779 on 24 June \u2014 before settling into a consolidation range broadly between 17.37 and 17.58. That range has been the dominant feature for the past three weeks, and price currently sits in the upper half of it, which is consistent with the desk's bullish read.\n\nThe structure story is one of base-building after a meaningful impulse move. The June breakout candle on the 23rd was decisive, clearing prior resistance and establishing a new higher range. Since then, dips have been bought. The zone around 17.4324 has registered six prior reactions \u2014 arguably the most significant structural support on the board \u2014 and price has not revisited it since the 15 July low of 17.3574, which itself found buyers quickly. The 17.5080 area, a prior reaction zone with three touches, is now the immediate floor beneath current price. The pair has been grinding along this level for much of the past week, and the fact that it has held on multiple tests gives it meaningful weight as near-term structural support.\n\nOn the H1 chart, the intraday picture is one of gradual softening from the overnight highs near 17.5556. Price drifted lower through the London morning, touching 17.5074 before stabilising. The hourly candles since then have been compressed and lacking conviction, suggesting neither side is pressing aggressively into the close. The 17.50\u201317.51 band is acting as an intraday floor, and any sustained hold above it keeps the short-term picture constructive. A failure to hold this zone on a closing basis would bring the 17.43 structure back into focus.\n\nThe calendar is empty today, which removes the risk of sharp event-driven moves in either direction. With no scheduled data releases for either the US or Mexico, price action is likely to remain technically driven and potentially subdued in terms of range. Thin conditions can occasionally amplify moves, but the absence of a catalyst makes a breakout of the recent range less probable in today's session alone.\n\nThe bullish read would come under pressure if price were to close a daily candle convincingly below the 17.5080 prior reaction zone, which would shift attention toward the 17.4324 multi-touch support. A break and close beneath that level would materially change the structural picture, suggesting the June breakout range is being unwound rather than consolidated. Conversely, a daily close above 17.60 would represent a meaningful reclaim of the upper portion of the range and strengthen the case for a retest of the June highs.\n\nThis is editorial analysis, not financial advice. Trading involves substantial risk of loss.", "sample": false}